00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.609
Preparing Your Home
for Professional Photos

00:00:03.150 --> 00:00:07.110
In this video, we will walk through how
to prepare your home so your listing

00:00:07.110 --> 00:00:12.519
photos look great, attract buyers, and
help prevent issues later in the process.

00:00:13.175 --> 00:00:16.444
Professional photos are one of the
most important parts of your listing.

00:00:17.385 --> 00:00:22.154
They are often the first impression
buyers get, so a little preparation

00:00:22.154 --> 00:00:24.584
ahead of time can make a big difference.

00:00:25.275 --> 00:00:26.314
Preparing Every Room

00:00:27.012 --> 00:00:28.362
Start with a thorough cleaning.

00:00:28.922 --> 00:00:32.482
Dust, vacuum, mop, and wipe down
surfaces throughout the home.

00:00:33.272 --> 00:00:36.242
Pay close attention to floors,
windows, and mirrors so everything

00:00:36.242 --> 00:00:38.202
looks clean and well maintained.

00:00:39.312 --> 00:00:43.092
Turn on all interior lights and
replace any burnt-out bulbs.

00:00:43.672 --> 00:00:46.292
Open curtains and blinds
to let in natural light.

00:00:46.612 --> 00:00:49.452
Bright rooms photograph
better and feel more inviting.

00:00:50.042 --> 00:00:52.012
Next, remove clutter and personal items.

00:00:52.382 --> 00:00:54.552
Clear off countertops,
tables, and shelves.

00:00:55.072 --> 00:00:59.012
Put away family photos, paperwork,
pet items, cords, trash cans, laundry

00:00:59.012 --> 00:01:00.512
baskets, and cleaning supplies.

00:01:01.172 --> 00:01:03.782
The goal is to help buyers
focus on the space itself.

00:01:04.450 --> 00:01:05.660
Kitchen and Bathrooms

00:01:06.175 --> 00:01:10.085
These rooms get a lot of attention
from buyers, so keep them simple.

00:01:10.875 --> 00:01:15.375
In the kitchen, clear countertops or leave
just one or two minimal decorative items.

00:01:15.684 --> 00:01:18.795
Clean appliances, sinks, and
backsplashes until they shine.

00:01:20.225 --> 00:01:24.784
In bathrooms, remove all toiletries,
close toilet lids, hang clean

00:01:24.784 --> 00:01:28.154
neutral towels, and make sure
mirrors and fixtures are spotless.

00:01:28.725 --> 00:01:30.124
Living Areas and Bedrooms

00:01:30.649 --> 00:01:35.010
Arrange furniture neatly and remove extra
pieces that make rooms feel crowded.

00:01:35.459 --> 00:01:37.749
Make all beds and turn off televisions.

00:01:38.412 --> 00:01:39.702
Exterior and Curb Appeal

00:01:40.387 --> 00:01:43.387
The outside of your home matters
just as much as the inside.

00:01:44.517 --> 00:01:47.547
Mow the lawn, trim bushes,
sweep walkways and driveways,

00:01:47.797 --> 00:01:49.307
and remove cars if possible.

00:01:50.107 --> 00:01:54.067
Clean exterior windows at least 48 hours
before photos are taken so they have

00:01:54.067 --> 00:01:55.907
time to dry and won’t appear streaky.

00:01:56.577 --> 00:01:59.087
Hide trash cans, hoses, tools, and toys.

00:01:59.899 --> 00:02:00.830
Pets and Access

00:02:01.349 --> 00:02:05.650
Photography equipment can be stressful
for pets, so plan to have them out

00:02:05.650 --> 00:02:07.299
of the home during the photo shoot.

00:02:07.999 --> 00:02:08.800
Conveying vs.

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:09.919
Non-Conveying Items

00:02:10.512 --> 00:02:12.992
This is an important step
many sellers overlook.

00:02:13.912 --> 00:02:17.382
Anything attached to the home is generally
assumed to stay with the property.

00:02:17.982 --> 00:02:21.682
This includes light fixtures,
ceiling fans, and mounted items.

00:02:22.387 --> 00:02:25.847
If there is something attached that
you plan to take with you, especially

00:02:25.847 --> 00:02:29.817
a sentimental fixture, we recommend
replacing it before photos are taken.

00:02:30.797 --> 00:02:34.977
Once an item appears in listing photos,
buyers expect it to be included.

00:02:36.067 --> 00:02:40.867
Swapping it out ahead of time helps avoid
confusion or negotiation issues later.

00:02:41.462 --> 00:02:45.152
Before the photographer arrives,
do one last walkthrough and look at

00:02:45.152 --> 00:02:47.032
your home from a buyer’s perspective.

00:02:47.942 --> 00:02:52.572
Taking these steps helps your photos
accurately represent your home and

00:02:52.572 --> 00:02:54.292
sets your listing up for success.

